{{Infobox football club | clubname = FC FIEL | image = | fullname = Futebol Clube Fitun Estudante Lorosae | nickname = | founded = {{Start date and age|2001}} | ground = [[National Stadium (East Timor)|Municipal Stadium]], [[Dili]] | capacity = 5,000 | chairman = | manager = [[Arsenio Afonsu]]| league = [[Liga Futebol Amadora|LFA2]] | season = [[2018 LFA Segunda|2018]] | position = | pattern_la1=|pattern_b1=|pattern_ra1=| leftarm1=|body1=|rightarm1=|shorts1=|socks1=| pattern_la2=|pattern_b2=|pattern_ra2=| leftarm2=|body2=|rightarm2=|shorts2=|socks2=| }}
'''Fitun Estudante Lorosae''' (in [[Tetum language|Tetum]] mean ''Star students of the east''), commonly known as '''FIEL'''<ref>[https://scontent-frt3-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/20799892_10207740162420868_5374630509552503686_n.jpg?oh=35b74ec4ba4ad6ae016f7625eb0d6f58&oe=5A26BFB2 Photo of a player with the abbreviation]</ref> is an [[East Timor]]ese football club based in [[Dili]]. The team plays in the [[Liga Futebol Amadora]].
==History== In early 2017, the creation of a third league was considered in East Timor. One of the team that talked about it was FC FIEL.<ref>Sportivo-news.com: SEJD Prontu Fasilita Kriasaun Terseira Divisaun ba LFA, 6. Februar 2017.</ref>
On 20 April 2017 by the League Futebol Amadora twelve teams were determined who could qualify in a tournament for the second division. One of them was FC FIEL.<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/ligafutebolamadora/photos/a.768197846635322.1073741828.768043906650716/1137405963047840/?type=3&theater Notifikasaun ba klube foun, hodi Submete Dokumentus no Lista Jogador]</ref>
The tournament took place from 16 to 31 May 2017. The FC FIEL managed there position on [[2018 LFA Segunda]] with a 2-0 victory against [[União Tokodede]] in the match for third place qualification.<ref>LFA: [https://www.facebook.com/ligafutebolamadora/posts/1175459665909136 JOGU APURAMENTU LIGA FUTEBOL AMADORA (LFA) BA EKIPA PROMOSAUN SEGUNDA DIVISAUN EPOCA 2018. FITUN ESTUDANTE PROMOVIDO BA SEGUNDA DIVISAUN EPOCA 2018]</ref>
==Honours== *Copa Presidente champions : 2004
