'''Howard Wood Field''' is a [[stadium]] in [[Sioux Falls, South Dakota]], constructed in 1957.<ref>{{cite web| last =| first =| authorlink =| coauthors =| title =Howard Wood Field| work =| publisher =City of Sioux Falls| date =| url =http://www.siouxfalls.org/Information/history/trivia/triva_questions/072| accessdate =2008-11-25| deadurl =yes| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20080906181613/http://www.siouxfalls.org/Information/history/trivia/triva_questions/072| archivedate =2008-09-06| df =}}</ref> Holding 10,000 people, it is one of the premier [[American football|football]], [[association football|soccer]] and [[Track and Field|track]] facilities in the region. Field turf was installed to replace the natural grass after a renovation project in 2003.<ref>[http://goaugie.com/section_front.asp?arttypeid=793 Augustana<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
==Events== Howard Wood Field is host to the Howard Wood Dakota Relays, an extended weekend of collegiate and High School track and field,and soccer competition.<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title =Howard Wood Dakota Relays | work = | publisher = | date = | url =http://dakotarelays.com/ | accessdate =2008-11-25 }}</ref> Howard Wood Field serves as host for the Bob Burns Dakota Bowl, an annual fundraiser for [[O'Gorman Catholic High School (Sioux Falls, South Dakota)|O'Gorman High School]], which is a Catholic school in Sioux Falls, South Dakota. The Bob Burns Dakota Bowl is focused around a football game between O'Gorman High School and another team chosen on a year by year basis. Additionally, Howard Wood Field is also host to the President's Bowl football games. The President's Bowl serves as a fundraiser for extra curricular activities for the Sioux Falls, South Dakota public High Schools. From 1993 through 2006 over $1.3 million has been raised from this annual set of football games. The stadium also serves as host to other track events as well as marching band competitions.
Howard Wood Field also serves as the home football stadium for all three Sioux Falls Public High Schools ([[Washington High School (Sioux Falls, South Dakota)|Washington]], [[Lincoln High School (Sioux Falls, South Dakota)|Lincoln]], and [[Roosevelt High School (Sioux Falls, South Dakota)|Roosevelt]]).
The [[Minnesota Vikings]] played their first game, an exhibition against the [[Dallas Cowboys]] on Aug. 5, 1961, at Howard Wood Field.<ref>{{cite web | last = Vikings.com | title= Series Notes vs. Cowboys | url=http://www.vikings.com/news/Game-Info-Centers/ps-4-09-cowboys.html | accessdate = 2009-11-12}}</ref> Legendary local football coach, Bob Burns, promoted the game.
On September 26, 2007, [[Augustana College (South Dakota)|Augustana College]] announced it would no longer call Howard Wood Field home, after a $6.1 million donation was given to allow the college to build an on-campus football facility, called the [[Kirkeby–Over Stadium]].<ref>[http://augie.edu/news/pressrel/2007/sept/1_26.htm Augustana News: Augustana to Build Football Stadium on Campus<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The school played at Howard Wood Field from 1958 to 2008.
