'''Lerissa Henry''' (born August 18, 1997) is a [[sprint (running)|sprinter]] from the [[Federated States of Micronesia]]. She competed at the [[2016 Summer Olympics]] in the [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Women's 100 metres|women's 100 metres]] race; her time of 13.53 seconds in the preliminary round did not qualify her for the first round.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lerissa Henry |url=https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/lerissa-henry |website=Rio 2016 |accessdate=August 22, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823014143/https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/lerissa-henry |archivedate=August 23, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Women's 100m - Standings |url=https://www.rio2016.com/en/athletics-standings-at-womens-100m |website=Rio 2016 |accessdate=August 22, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160814121037/https://www.rio2016.com/en/athletics-standings-at-womens-100m |archivedate=August 14, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>

