{{Infobox basketball league |name = Eurovia SBL |image = Eurovia SBL logo.png |pixels = |country = {{SVK}} |other countries= |confed = [[FIBA Europe]] |founded = 1993 |first = 1993 |folded = |divisions = |teams = 10 |feeds = |promotion = |relegation = 1. Liga |levels = 1 |domest_cup = [[Slovak Basketball Cup|Slovak Cup]] |supercup = |overseas_tournament= [[FIBA Europe Cup]] |confed_cup = |champions =[[BK Levickí|Levickí Patrioti]] (2nd title) |season = |most_champs = [[MBK Pezinok|Pezinok]] (9 titles) |top_scorer = |tv = |sponsor = Eurovia |website = {{URL|http://www.basketliga.sk/}} |current = [[2018–19 Slovak Basketball League]] }} The '''Slovenská Basketbalová Liga (SBL)''' ({{lang-en|'''Slovak Basketball League'''}}) is the highest level tier league of men's professional club [[basketball]] in [[Slovakia]]. The league was founded in 1993. [[MBK Pezinok]] is the league's most successful team, having won a league record 9 championships. Before 2014, the league was named the '''Extraliga'''.
