'''Sofiia Lyskun''' ({{lang-uk|Софія Лискун}}; born 7 February 2002) is a Ukrainian [[Diving (sport)|diver]], medalist of the European Championships.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://day.kyiv.ua/uk/news/140617-ukrayina-vyborola-tretyu-medal-na-domashnomu-chye-zi-strybkiv-u-vodu|title=Україна виборола третю медаль на домашньому ЧЄ зі стрибків у воду|language=Ukrainian|date=14 June 2017}}</ref> She won a bronze medal in 10-meter platform synchro diving (with [[Valeriia Liulko]]) at the [[2017 European Diving Championships]] in [[Kyiv]] and a gold in the [[Diving at the 2018 European Aquatics Championships – Team|team event]] (with [[Oleh Kolodiy]]) at the multi-event [[2018 European Championships]] in [[Glasgow]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/diving/40286193|website=[[BBC]]|title=European Diving Championships: Ruby Bower & Phoebe Banks win gold for GB|date=15 June 2017}}</ref>

