{{Infobox stadium | name = Stade Francis-Le Basser | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Stade Francis le basser.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1971 | renovated = 2002 | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Agglomeration community of the Laval agglomeration|Laval Agglomeration]] | operator = | surface = grass | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 18,739 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = [[Stade Lavallois]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''Stade Francis Le Basser''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Laval, Mayenne|Laval]], [[France]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Stade Lavallois]]. The stadium is able to hold 18,739 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldstadiums.com/europe/countries/france/pays_de_la_loire.shtml |title=Stadiums in France Pays de la Loire|publisher=Worldstadiums.com|accessdate=7 November 2011}}</ref>
