{{infobox country at games | NOC = VEN | NOCname = [[Venezuelan Olympic Committee]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1968 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.covoficial.com.ve }}&nbsp;{{es icon}} | location = [[Mexico City]] | competitors = 23 | sports = 5 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 1 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = 1948 | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Venezuela]]''' competed at the '''[[1968 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]]. [[Francisco Rodríguez (boxer)|Francisco Rodríguez]] won the nation's first ever gold medal. 23 competitors, all men, took part in 17 events in 5 sports.<ref name="sports-reference">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/VEN/summer/1968/ |title=Venezuela at the 1968 Mexico City Summer Games |accessdate=2011-01-03 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>
==Medalists== ===Gold=== * [[Francisco Rodríguez (boxer)|Francisco Rodríguez]] &mdash; Boxing, Men's Light Flyweight (&ndash; 48&nbsp;kg)
==Athletics== {{main|Athletics at the 1968 Summer Olympics}}
==Boxing== {{main|Boxing at the 1968 Summer Olympics}} '''Men's Light Flyweight (– 48&nbsp;kg)''' *[[Francisco Rodríguez (boxer)|Francisco Rodríguez]] :* First Round &mdash; Bye :* Second Round &mdash; Defeated [[Rafael Carbonell]] (CUB), 5:0 :* Quarterfinals &mdash; Defeated [[Khata Karunatarne]] (CEY), TKO-2 :* Semifinals &mdash; Defeated [[Harlan Marbley]] (USA), 4:1 :* Final &mdash; Defeated [[Jee Yong-Ju]] (KOR), 3:2
